BrasÃ­lia (DF) Filtering

The Federal District (BrasÃ­lia) has a special electoral status: - No municipal elections: As a Federal District, BrasÃ­lia does not hold mayoral or city council elections - Federal/State elections only: Participates only in presidential, gubernatorial, senatorial, and legislative elections (every 4 years)

Filtering Applied: - BrasÃ­lia polling stations have been removed from municipal election years (2008, 2012, 2016, 2020, 2024) - This filtering ensures accurate municipality counts and prevents false anomalies in year-over-year comparisons
